&lt;p&gt;Previous applicants need not apply&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;15 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: TBA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Musculoskeletal Therapy team at Queens and King Georges Hospital offer assessment and treatment to MSK patients referred by Consultants and GPs across our 3 London Boroughs. We are now looking for a member of staff to contribute to the growth and development of the service. Working in collaboration with GPs, Orthopaedic, Rheumatology, Neurosurgery (spinal) and Pain Consultants we are looking for an individual who is forward thinking and will be integral in contributing to the future shape of the MSK ESP service at the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have the skills outlined below and want a rewarding opportunity where you will be encouraged to be innovative whilst being valued and supported then apply today.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a post for an ambitious, motivated MSK clinician with excellent communication skills, dynamic leadership skills and expert assessment and treatment skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential criteria&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree/Diploma in Physiotherapy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidence of relevant MSc or M-level qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HCPC registration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leadership experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience Musculoskeletal Outpatients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All new staff appointed to posts at the Trust will be subject to a 6 months probationary period. This will give new staff members an opportunity to become familiar with the culture and working environment of the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications should be made online, however, queries regarding the application process or assistance with completion of the form (for applicants with a disability) can be made to Zeshaan Beg Recruitment Department on 01708 435000 ext 2286. Further details regarding the post may be obtained by contacting the manager please see below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Marie Loizides Therapy Manager via e-mail Marie.Loizides@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
